# Chronos-328: Standalone ATmega328P Embedded Countdown & Development Platform

## Project Overview
Chronos-328 is an open-source, standalone microcontroller evaluation board built around the **Microchip ATmega328P** 8-bit AVR architecture. This project details the transition from a verified Proteus simulation to a fully realized, routed PCB architecture featuring an integrated USB-to-UART serial interface, a robust regulated power supply stage, and multi-bus display hardware.

The integrated firmware manages a synchronous countdown routine utilizing an I2C OLED display and a 74HC595 shift-register-driven Common Cathode 7-segment display alongside synchronized audio-visual feedback mechanisms.

### Core System Features
1. **Processor Core:** Standalone ATmega328P clocked by an external 16MHz crystal oscillator network.
2. **On-Board Programmer:** Full FT232RL USB-to-UART circuit with data line conditioning and an automatic DTR bootloader reset circuit.
3. **Power Subsystem:** 5V Linear regulation stage via an L7805 footprint, incorporating reverse-polarity protection and transient-filtering decoupling networks.
4. **User Interface Module:** Simultaneous execution of high-speed I2C communication (128x64 OLED) and SPI-like bit-shifting (74HC595 Driving a 7-Segment Display).

