## Firmware Implementation

The control logic checks the hardware status flags immediately upon boot to handle reset visual indicators, and transitions into non-blocking timing states for the countdown.

### Logic Flow Diagram

[Power On] ──> Read MCUSR Register ──> Flag EXTRF? ──> [YES] ──> Display "RESET"
│
[NO]
▼
Display "START"
│
▼
Display "LOADING..."
│
▼
9 to 0 Loop Intercept
(Segment Countdown + Buzzer Pulse)
│
▼
Display "END"
(Continuous Alarm Trigger)

